204 National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2024, Section 251 ("Congressional notification of changes to Department of Defense policy on autonomy in weapon systems") FY2024 NDAA, Section 251 ("Congressional notification of changes to Department of Defense policy on autonomy in weapon systems") www.congress.gov/bill/118th-congress/house-bill/2670/text United States Congress NDAA provisions;Enacted laws and policies;U.S. federal laws Enacted 2023-12-22 00:00:00 NaT True False Requires the Secretary of Defense to brief the congressional defense committees on the nature and purpose of any modifications to Department of Defense Directive 300.09, which relates to autonomy in weapons systems.  Requires the Secretary of Defense to brief the congressional defense committees on the nature and purpose of any modifications to Department of Defense Directive 300.09, which relates to autonomy in weapons systems, within 30 days of making the modifications. SEC. 251. CONGRESSIONAL NOTIFICATION OF CHANGES TO DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE POLICY ON AUTONOMY IN WEAPON SYSTEMS.

Not later than 30 days after making a modification to Department of Defense Directive 3000.09 (relating to autonomy in weapon systems) the Secretary of Defense shall provide to the congressional defense committees a briefing that includes--
	(1) a description of the modification; and
	(2) an explanation of the reasons for the modification. Requires the Secretary of Defense to brief Congress on modifications to autonomy in weapon systems policy. sec. 251. congressional notification of changes to department of defense policy on autonomy in weapon systems. not later than 30 days after making a modification to department of defense directive 3000.09 (relating to autonomy in weapon systems) the secretary of defense shall provide to the congressional defense committees a briefing that includes-- (1) a description of the modification; and (2) an explanation of the reasons for the modification.